President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring September 8-14, 2019, as National Minority Enterprise Development Week. The proclamation recognizes the success of minority-owned businesses and their significant role in strengthening the country's economy. It highlights the 50th anniversary of the Minority Business Development Agency (MBDA) and the growth of the minority population over the years. The proclamation also mentions the President's efforts to ensure prosperity for all Americans, including regulatory reform, tax cuts, and the creation of opportunity zones. It emphasizes the importance of innovation, policy development, and job training in preparing minority-owned businesses for emerging industries. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to celebrate the week with programs, ceremonies, and activities that recognize the contributions of minority business enterprises.